<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2247] [performance] Small scans should run like a random-read</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2247</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;hbase-2180 added pread whenever we do a get &amp;#8211; random-read &amp;#8211; and kept the old sync+position+read for when scanning.   In between is the case of small scans.  Small scans of 0-100 or so rows where the cells are small will likely fit a single hfile blocksize, especially if its the default 64k.  We should recognize small scans and flip to random-read to satisfy (somehow).  It&apos;ll up the performance a bit.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
